ast.name: RPN Calculator
ast.comment:
A scientific HP-like pocket calculator with a four-level stack and one storage register. All offered functionality should work now. Any bug reports or improvement suggestions are highly welcome.

This version adds rudimentary display formatting.

h7sjauOa7qBVfedGD4VUXYcm.text: Visual feedback for the pressed key:

OouGA9axoBT4YI8zh0wa0yui.text: 1: transform (x,y) to (x',y') after entering a point

Ta0WUc5UeeIG6qZQIKD2pOAf.text: 2: transform (a',b') to (a,b) after calculating the linear regression

f2DZ3FkMOdwwIaih2JxV669p.text: linear form is: ln y = ln a + bx

atShgt2sdWzjW4arkQlW9255.text: linear form is: ln y = ln a + b ln x

fK7W2nMl3a5uTKYyRmk8Ya0d.text: linear form is: y/x = a + bx

jrl0skuZMJY7P9mPxTSFf0bf.text: linear form is: y/x = a + bx²

x422DUhwBamVUbMsuulDEU3l.text: linear form is: y/x² = a + bx

LL9041vP45BFxXQTLoao1SQk.text: linear form is: arc sin y = a + bx

d20Y152xsXdvl1wh5KfCG8Vz.text: linear form is: y / cos² x = a + b tan² x

app.comment: A HP-like pocket calculator with a four-level stack and reverse polish notation (see http://www.hpmuseum.org/rpn.htm). Online help: Press g, ? to read the manual. This is all integrated. Web access is only needed to open the above http link directly from the help pages, not to read the manual. 2012-10-18: ROUND now rounds to display settings, as stated in online help (always rounded to whole numbers previously). Fixed y^ calculation for y=ax+bx³ correlation function. Additional quadratic trigonometric correlation function (13 in total now). Plus some minor refinements.

A HP-like programmable pocket calculator with a four-level stack and reverse polish notation (see http://www.hpmuseum.org/rpn.htm). Online help: Press g, ? to read the manual. This is all integrated. Web access is only needed to open the above http link directly from the help pages, not to read the manual. 2012-10-30: The calculator is fully programmable, very similar to the classic programmable HP pocket calculators. Please see the help pages for detailed information.

A HP-like programmable pocket calculator with a four-level stack and reverse polish notation (see http://www.hpmuseum.org/rpn.htm). Online help: Press g, ? to read the manual. This is all integrated. Web access is only needed to open the above http link directly from the help pages, not to read the manual. 2013-04-08: Fixed: STO × and STO ÷ did not work any more since using the new nicer symbols × and ÷. Also, the new symbols are now used consistently in the online help text.

A HP-like programmable pocket calculator with a four-level stack and reverse polish notation (see http://www.hpmuseum.org/rpn.htm). Online help: Press g, ? to read the manual. This is all integrated. Web access is only needed to open the above http link directly from the help pages, not to read the manual. 2013-04-16: Fixed: CHS as unary function on SST in fast execution mode did not update the display. New: SHOW offers two listing formats for display and clipboard copy.

A HP-like programmable pocket calculator with a four-level stack and reverse polish notation (see http://www.hpmuseum.org/rpn.htm). Online help: Press g, ? to read the manual. This is all integrated. Web access is only needed to open the above http link directly from the help pages, not to read the manual. 2013-04-27: A ton of new features, enabled through a third keyboard layout with a new row of keys: Subroutines (XEQ/RTN), definable function keys A - E, more comparisons (and displaying YES/NO when used interactively), TIME function, PSE instruction, CAP allows for definable captions for numbers, ten flags (set/reset/test), flag 9 indicates number entry, performance work. All documented in the help text.

A HP-like programmable pocket calculator with a four-level stack and reverse polish notation (see http://www.hpmuseum.org/rpn.htm). Online help: Press g, ? to read the manual. This is all integrated. Web access is only needed to open the above http link directly from the help pages, not to read the manual. 2013-05-26: Introduced indirect operations for storage, flags and display formatting. Up to 100 storage registers. Paste programs copied with the SHOW command back into the calculator. See help for details.

A HP-like programmable pocket calculator with a four-level stack and reverse polish notation (see http://www.hpmuseum.org/rpn.htm). Online help: Press g, ? to read the manual. This is all integrated. Web access is only needed to open the above http link directly from the help pages, not to read the manual. 2013-06-07: Fixed: Recording SF or CF not only recorded the step, but also executed it. New: RCL Σ+ recalls statistic sums into the stack registers.

Web access is only needed to open the above http link directly from the help pages, not to read the manual. 2013-08-05: Added support for stack addressing command variants like RCL Z, STO + IND Y, FS?
